 no classpath entries available. This definitely requires careful handling of dependencies when working with native images!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Hibernate Dependencies**\\n\\nI need to ensure that Class.forName has access to the necessary Hibernate classes during test runtime. To do this, I’ll add the hibernate-core dependency. It looks like the JPAConfiguration class will need JPA, likely through hibernate-core. Although Hibernate 5.6 relies on javax.persistence-api 2.2, the test source might not be importing JPA. We may also need to define annotation arguments and load javax.persistence classes through hibernate-core, possibly with an explicit inclusion of jakarta.persistence-api. That seems wise.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_zxIh44WCHPmYyWpWxrDlOYAf|fc_02e09efad86dd3ce016a02d789643c81a3a5498533d79d1746", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.querydsl/querydsl-apt/5.0.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json", "limit": 100}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 813, "output": 2114, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22895, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778571112572, "responseId": "resp_02e09efad86dd3ce016a02d7693a5481a3b0f8d6a3712e3a43"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_zxIh44WCHPmYyWpWxrDlOYAf|fc_02e09efad86dd3ce016a02d789643c81a3a5498533d79d1746", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"classes\" : [ {\n    \"callSites\" : [ {\n      \"covered\" : false,\n      \"frame\" : \"com.querydsl.apt.hibernate.HibernateConfiguration.getAnnotations(HibernateConfiguration.java:52)\",\n      \"line\" : 52,\n      \"metadataType\" : \"reflection\",\n      \"trackedApi\" : \"java.lang.Class#forName(java.lang.String)\"\n    } ],\n    \"className\" : \"com.querydsl.apt.hibernate.HibernateConfigu