ential assertion issues**\\n\\nI’m noticing a potential issue where the processor catches Throwable and returns false; if the failure occurs, task.call might be true, leading to an assertion failure that prints out a message. I think using `assertThat(processor.failure).isNull()` could effectively show that. It might also be important to ensure that I include a check for `annotationNames` being not null, since containing on a null value would fail the assertion. Let's keep this in mind!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting image classpath**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the native image classpath includes a jar file, which is interesting. There might be a potential issue with the agent metadata generated for the Hibernate classes, but I see that the user-code-filter only includes Querydsl. It's worth taking a closer look to understand how this might affect the overall functionality. I’ll dig deeper into this to see if there are any underlying problems!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jOy1rBANQci2CfZ3Pxa8j8ZS|fc_02e09efad86dd3ce016a02d7aeb74881a388a54ec4754421ba", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.querydsl/querydsl-apt/5.0.0/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 265, "output": 855, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27232, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778571167386, "responseId": "resp_02e09efad86dd3ce016a02d7a00e5881a389dde259cdfe6ac9"}}
